WEBVTT

00:01.536 --> 00:03.002
I just heard you turned down a client

00:03.038 --> 00:05.359
whose investment firm
is worth $2 billion.

00:05.459 --> 00:06.238
Well, I don't give a shit
how much they're worth.

00:06.274 --> 00:08.709
I'm not representing William Sutter.

00:08.953 --> 00:09.752
I didn't kill anyone.

00:10.529 --> 00:12.162
I've been saying it for 12 years,

00:12.197 --> 00:13.997
and I can prove it.

00:14.033 --> 00:15.999
Do you want to take a
chance on each other or not?

00:16.035 --> 00:17.568
I just got a visit from Sean Cahill.

00:17.603 --> 00:20.003
It turns out there's a
way he can get you out.

00:20.039 --> 00:21.204
What's the catch?

00:21.239 --> 00:23.006
He needs you to inform
on your cellmate.

00:23.042 --> 00:25.042
- Tell me the truth.
- He said no.

00:25.077 --> 00:26.810
But Sean, I'm telling
you, he'll come around.

00:26.845 --> 00:28.078
Do you know how many strings I pulled

00:28.113 --> 00:29.746
to put this thing in motion?

00:29.782 --> 00:31.181
You're gonna get me out
of here like you promised.

00:31.216 --> 00:32.381
I never promised...

00:32.417 --> 00:33.917
Six weeks, brother,

00:33.953 --> 00:35.552
and if I find out you're screwing me,

00:35.588 --> 00:38.388
you better hole up in some
dark corner of this prison.

00:38.423 --> 00:40.090
How would you feel about
renovating my summer house

00:40.125 --> 00:41.892
- in the Hamptons?
- Are you sure?

00:41.927 --> 00:43.560
I've never been as sure of
anything in my entire life.

00:43.596 --> 00:45.495
The whole time, you were
always gonna bring him here.

00:45.530 --> 00:47.163
Because this is the
way to get it done.

00:47.199 --> 00:49.199
Then why didn't you tell
me that in the first place?

00:49.234 --> 00:51.434
Because it would've ended up
with you wanting to use Rachel.

00:51.470 --> 00:55.038
It ended there anyway. Now
get the hell out of my way.

00:55.074 --> 00:57.273
Harvey!

00:57.309 --> 01:00.443
I told Rachel everything.

01:00.479 --> 01:02.079
I'm taking the deal.

01:06.179 --> 01:07.879
All right, let's talk specifically

01:07.914 --> 01:09.146
about what you need.

01:09.182 --> 01:10.915
What I need is a conviction.

01:10.950 --> 01:13.251
Obviously, but what
exactly does that look like

01:13.286 --> 01:14.986
- from my side?
- It looks like a smoking gun,

01:15.021 --> 01:16.721
'cause I've been after
Sutter for three years now.

01:16.757 --> 01:18.222
This guy's one slippery son of a bitch.

01:18.258 --> 01:20.224
Wait a second. William Sutter?

01:20.260 --> 01:21.225
Are you kidding me?

01:21.261 --> 01:22.560
Harvey, what's going on?

01:22.596 --> 01:25.229
He came to me a week ago to
take him on, and I said no.

01:25.265 --> 01:26.898
Well, it's a good thing you did.

01:26.933 --> 01:28.900
- No, it isn't.
- What are you talking about?

01:28.935 --> 01:30.935
When Kevin finds out I
told his father-in-law

01:30.970 --> 01:32.837
to drop dead, he's never
gonna trust Mike.

01:32.873 --> 01:34.272
If you're saying what
I think you're saying,

01:34.307 --> 01:35.940
you're not taking this
man as your client.

01:35.975 --> 01:37.809
Yes, I am, because if I don't,

01:37.844 --> 01:39.611
we might as well not even be doing this.

01:39.646 --> 01:41.946
- Then let's not do it.
- Look where we are, Sean.

01:41.981 --> 01:43.981
We're in a car, sneaking
Mike into prison.

01:44.017 --> 01:46.083
You pulled every string you
have to make this happen.

01:46.119 --> 01:47.685
You're gonna pull out now?

01:47.721 --> 01:48.820
I am, 'cause I'm not gonna put myself

01:48.855 --> 01:50.087
in position to collude with you.

01:50.123 --> 01:51.523
I won't put you in that position.

01:51.558 --> 01:52.924
I'm in that position right now.

01:52.959 --> 01:54.292
No, you're not.

01:54.327 --> 01:55.827
He isn't even representing anybody yet.

01:55.862 --> 01:57.829
This conversation is
completely hypothetical.

01:57.864 --> 01:59.898
I don't need legal
advice from the convict,

01:59.933 --> 02:01.533
and I don't need to lose my career

02:01.568 --> 02:03.234
because you tanked this guy's defense.

02:03.269 --> 02:04.869
I'm not tanking anything.

02:04.905 --> 02:06.905
I'm gonna kick ass for him
up and down the block,

02:06.940 --> 02:08.806
and there's no law against
me rooting for Mike

02:08.842 --> 02:11.476
while I'm doing that.

02:11.511 --> 02:14.879
Okay, but you cross one line
that puts me in jeopardy,

02:14.915 --> 02:16.748
I'm gonna pull the plug
on this whole thing.

02:16.783 --> 02:18.716
Well, Mike better get us what we need

02:18.752 --> 02:20.585
before I have to do that.

